<br>
I read a post somewhere, can't remember exactly where at the moment, that postulated that Mob ATK is calculated differently than player ATK so FoR might not have an effect on a Mob's ATK.  I guess if that is true then  this would make this spell only useful, with respect to the ATK component, on PVP server.  Right? <p>Robart Defuego <BR>
Please, please! This is supposed to be a happy occasion!<BR>
Let's not bicker and argue about who killed who.<BR>
Semi-retired druid, but still lurking.<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urumil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rumil</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/18/01 5:16:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2495.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.e-corridor.com/images/EQ/tinyrumil.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fixation of Ro</span><hr size=1> Does it work like a shamen slow, yes.<br>
<br>
Does it stack with a shamen slow, dont know that yet.<br>
<br>
I like it. <p>Warden of Tunare<br>
Wanderer of the 52nd Ring<br>
Innoruuk Server<br>
"Just once or twice its good for your Soul." ~ Oingo Boingo
<br><img src="http://www.ecorridor.com/images/EQ/deathpoketext.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubatou062671.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Batou062671</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/18/01 6:30:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2495.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fixation of Ro</span><hr size=1> From my useing Fixation of Ro, I've never noticed any 'slow' from the spell.  In fact, the tank said he noticed hardly any difference in the damage the mobs were doing to him with our without Fixation of Ro being cast.<br>
<br>
The spell reduces attack rating.  This is not the speed at which the mob attacks, but the value compared against the AC of the mob I belive. <p>Batou Thornhill<BR>
Preserver of the 55th Season<BR>
Harbingers<BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukulothar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kulothar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/19/01 9:03:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2495.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fixation of Ro</span><hr size=1> Yes it stacks.  But it doen't slow the mob, it debuffs his AC and ATK.   I use this continually on raids along with RFS depending on the group structure..   FoR is to Tanks what RFS is to casters..<br>
<br>
Your tanks may not say they notice an affect but you can see a big change in how fast the HP bar drops on the mob after casting it.    By dropping the AC and ATK, your tanks do more damage (more hits for more pts) and the mob hits for less (more misses or less damage when hit).   Definately one of my favorite raid spells for Kael or the Planes.   Was sticking it on mobs consistantly in Hate last night except for red's that resisted everything except for RFS.   <br>
<br>
It agros as much as Snare or RFS and if you cast any combo on the mob he WILL summon you.   <p><a href=mailto:karl_saffell@hotmail.com>Kulothar</a></br>
<a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bdragonmawguild><b>Dragon Maw</b></a></br>
I am not a TANK!!
I am an APC!! </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umanolas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Manolas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/20/01 5:38:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2495.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://manolasautumnleaf.homestead.com/files/dancing_sheep.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fixation of Ro</span><hr size=1> <br>
   Having several high level druids one of us usually casts<br>
   Ro's Fiery Sundering and the other usually casts Fixation<br>
   of Ro. We split it up if possible because if one does both<br>
   you'll definately over aggro the mob. Druid + over aggro'd<br>
   mob = dead druid.<br>
<br>
   Though there is no huge effect from this spell its the case<br>
   of 'every little bit helps'.<br>
<br>
   Manolas Autumnlead<br>
   Hierophant, Cazic Thule<br>
   Officer of Second Age <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utuene.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tuene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/25/01 4:24:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2495.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fixation of Ro</span><hr size=1> I'm a believer in the &quot;every little bit helps&quot; principle when it comes to EQ and debuffs on mobs (especially as there's an obnoxious number of druids in my guild heh), but has anyone ever conducted a test on parsing a mob's and melee's damage output to see if this spell makes a marked difference or not?<br>
<br>
Tuene<br>
Sol Ro <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uleandrawoodwinds1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leandra Woodwinds1</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/28/01 4:02:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2495.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Fixation of Ro</span><hr size=1> I use this spell a lot during raids, but it is a high aggro spell, and when you combine it with SNARE you will have one very dead druid (unless you have an awesome cleric).<br>
<br>
I was under the impression that it also debuffed FR, but I could be wrong /shrug.  Just the ATK and AC component for me is worth it =) <p><BR> Leandra  Woodwinds - Druid, 57  <BR> Kalynn Velvetblade -  Rogue, 32 <BR>
